{"questionId":"33297872","questionHtml":"<p>The following diagram shows triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABC</mtext></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>BC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>C</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></math>.<br><br></p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/e259066860d7ff66d49ebf1d1476192e2ff9732c.png\" width=\"705\" height=\"172\"><br>Find the exact value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>, giving your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msqrt><mi>p</mi></msqrt><mi>q</mi></mfrac></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute into cosine rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>45</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>45</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>105</mn><mn>120</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mo>±</mo></mfenced><msqrt><mfrac><mn>105</mn><mn>120</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>14</mn></msqrt><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The final answer must be positive.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33297872","referenceCode":"24N.1.SL.TZ1.5","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The following diagram shows triangle ABC, where AB=3 cm, BC=10 cm, AC=8 cm and AB^C=2θ. Find the exact value of cos θ, giving your answer in the form pq, where p, q∈ℤ+.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Pythagorean identity, double angles"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}